Miles nye amesi "xɔ ŋkɔreputation le bubudeameŋu mɔ dzi" eye wo woyɔnɛ be "[[:en:Stirling_Moss|Stirling Moss]] of the West Coast".<ref>{{Cite news|title=Biographical Sketches of Drivers|last=Canadian Racing Drivers Association|date=1964|work=Player's 200 Media Kit}}</ref> Esi wonɔ  kple AC-Cobra Ford Haboboa la, Miles geɖe [[:en:Lotus_23|Lotus 23]] me le ƒé 1964 Player's 200 le [[:en:Mosport|Mosport]]. 
[[File:Ford_GT40_(rear).jpg|right|thumb|GT40 Mk II megbe]]
Le ƒé 1965 me la, ezã [[:en:Ford_GT40#Mk_II|Ford GT Mk.II]] mɔ̃a kple [[:en:Bruce_McLaren|Bruce McLaren]] le [[:en:1965_24_Hours_of_Le_Mans|24 Hours of Le Mans]] gake exɔ dzudzɔ esi  eƒe gearbox gblẽ. Le ƒéa ƒe gɔmedzedzea me la, eya kple McLaren, exe nɔƒe evelia esi wo ʋli ho le[[:en:12_Hours_of_Sebring|12 Hours of Sebring]].

Esi ƒé trɔ la, ekpɔ dziɖuɖu le 24 Hours of Daytona ho ʋiʋlia me esi wozã  Ford GT Mk.II mɔ̃a kple Lloyd Ruby, eyidzi kpɔ dziɖuɖu le 12 Hours of Sebring ho ʋiʋlia hã me. Le ɣleti aɖewo megbe l esi woʋli ho kple Denny Hulme la, Miles ganɔ 1966 24 Hours of Le Mans kplɔm, esi Ford megã Leo Beebe, doe kplikpa be yea wɔawɔ gbeƒãɖeɖe le ʋu etɔ̃aaɖewo ƒe nutata siwo wowɔ vɔvɔvɔ la ŋti  la ena gbe bel [[:en:Carroll_Shelby|Carroll Shelby]] ne bɔbɔ ɖe eme si dzi Shelby lɔ̃ ɖo. Eyata le Ford ʋu si wo gawɔ si Bruce McLaren/Chris Amon  kuna la eye woxɔ nɔfe etɔlia le Ford ƒe mɔ̃awo  ɖome si wo kple vea ɖitsa kple. The French race officials, after initially agreeing to Ford's dead-heat "photo-finish", reneged during the final hour of the race.  McLaren's #2 car crossed the finish line just ahead and was declared the winner. It was rumoured that Miles, upset about the team orders, lifted off to allow McLaren to finish a length ahead. Miles was denied the unique achievement of winning Sebring, Daytona, and Le Mans in the same year.

